3. REMEDIATION RECOMMENDATION
* How would you fix the BOLA vulnerability?
Answer: Implement server-side authorization checks that
  verify the authenticated user owns the requested
  resource. Never trust user-supplied IDs alone. Use
  session tokens to confirm ownership before returning
  any profile data.

* How would you fix the Brute-Force vulnerability in the discount field?
Answer: Implement rate limiting on the checkout endpoint
  to block repeated requests. Use unpredictable discount
  codes instead of sequential numbers. Add expiry times
  on all codes and lock out after failed attempts.
